    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Status or condition of having been designed for viewing or use from both sides; examples are in reference to a relatively flat or two dimensional object, such as a work on paper or a textile.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
